![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The current initialization logic prevents the 'All States' filter (represented by an empty string) from persisting across page refreshes. Since `initial.get('status')` returns `""` when the parameter is present but empty, the `|| 'open'` fallback incorrectly resets it to `'open'`. 

To fix this, check for `null` explicitly during initialization and update the `syncUrl` logic to include the status in the URL whenever it differs from the default ('open').

```suggestion
  const [status, setStatus] = useState(() => {
    const fromUrl = initial.get('status');
    return fromUrl !== null ? fromUrl : 'open';
  });
```

The `status` state is not validated against the allowed values and defaults via `|| 'open'`, which makes it impossible to reflect a URL like `?status=` (intended to mean 'All States'). Also, if `?status=<unknown>` is present, the `<select value={status}>` won’t match any option, creating an inconsistent UI state and potentially filtering to zero results. Parse/validate the initial status (e.g., allow '' or one of `PROPOSAL_STATUSES`, otherwise default), and avoid relying on `toLowerCase()` as the validator.
```suggestion
                const raw = event.target.value;
                const nextStatus =
                  raw === '' || PROPOSAL_STATUSES.includes(raw as (typeof PROPOSAL_STATUSES)[number])
                    ? raw
                    : '';
                setStatus(nextStatus);
```
